import cv2
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load images
sparrow_image = cv2.imread('/Users/shiveshrajsahu/Desktop/Cs767/cs767A1_SAHU_SHIVESH_HW05/Unknown.jpeg')
sky_image = cv2.imread('/Users/shiveshrajsahu/Desktop/Cs767/cs767A1_SAHU_SHIVESH_HW05/Unknown2.jpeg')

# Convert from BGR to RGB (OpenCV loads images in BGR format)
sparrow_image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(sparrow_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
sky_image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(sky_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

# Display the images
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))

ax[0].imshow(sparrow_image_rgb)
ax[0].set_title('Sparrow Image')
ax[0].axis('off')

ax[1].imshow(sky_image_rgb)
ax[1].set_title('Sky Image')
ax[1].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Resize the sparrow image to match the sky image dimensions
if sparrow_image.shape != sky_image.shape:
    sparrow_image_resized = cv2.resize(sparrow_image, (sky_image.shape[1], sky_image.shape[0]))
else:
    sparrow_image_resized = sparrow_image

# Convert the resized image from BGR to RGB for display
sparrow_image_resized_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(sparrow_image_resized, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

# Display the resized image
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
plt.imshow(sparrow_image_resized_rgb)
plt.title('Resized Sparrow Image')
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()
In [3]:
# Define weight combinations for blending
weights = [(0.2, 0.8), (0.3, 0.7), (0.4, 0.6), (0.5, 0.5), (0.6, 0.4)]

blended_images = []

# Blend images using different weight combinations
for weight in weights:
    blended = cv2.addWeighted(sparrow_image_resized, weight[0], sky_image, weight[1], 0)
    blended_images.append(blended)

# Display blended images
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, len(weights), figsize=(15, 5))
for i, (img, weight) in enumerate(zip(blended_images, weights)):
    ax[i].imshow(cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    ax[i].set_title(f'Weights: {weight[0]} & {weight[1]}')
    ax[i].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
